{"type":"message","id":"cd0d5e71","parentId":"60f5fa91","timestamp":"2026-06-01T06:46:15.226Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The headed browser is running on the server and waiting for QR code scan. Since I can't send the image to the user via Feishu (image processing is broken), I need another plan.\n\nOptions:\n1. Save the screenshot elsewhere and try to send the file path\n2. Kill this session and try yet another approach\n3. Use a simpler method - the user already has DevOps logged into Chrome. Let me just try to extract cookies from Chrome's local storage.\n\nActually, let me think about this differently. The user's Chrome has the full session. Maybe I can use a Playwright script that reads Chrome's actual user data directory to extract cookies. Or I could try to find Chrome's cookie file directly.\n\nOn Windows, Chrome stores cookies in:\n`C:\\Users\\%USERNAME%\\AppData\\Local\\Google\\Chrome\\User Data\\Default\\Cookies`\n\nBut this is a SQLite database and it's encrypted... very tricky.\n\nLet me kill this process and try another approach. The user said they already logged into DevOps in Chrome - maybe they can use an extension like \"EditThisCookie\" or \"Get cookies.txt\" to export all cookies for the devcloud domains.\n\nActually, I have a better idea. Let me try to extract cookies from the user's Chrome by launching Playwright with `--user-data-dir` pointing to the user's Chrome profile.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_g54fgW3wBy7ArEyIDbRj8290","name":"process","arguments":{"sessionId":"marine-slug","action":"kill"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":146,"output":344,"cacheRead":42112,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":42602,"cost":{"input":0.00002044,"output":0.00009632000000000001,"cacheRead":0.001179136,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.001295896}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780296371414,"responseId":"2dfa4d7c-228