{"type":"custom_message","customType":"openclaw.runtime-context","content":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"chat_id\": \"user:ou_6509d346e8d50ef882f89c436e6c977f\",\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b6ee0528094b4b2781b2bef57a99\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_6509d346e8d50ef882f89c436e6c977f\",\n  \"sender\": \"Yousan(叶枝君)\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Mon 2026-06-01 16:24 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"Yousan(叶枝君) (ou_6509d346e8d50ef882f89c436e6c977f)\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_6509d346e8d50ef882f89c436e6c977f\",\n  \"name\": \"Yousan(叶枝君)\"\n}\n```","display":false,"details":{"source":"openclaw-runtime-context"},"id":"22a69cae","parentId":"187241a8","timestamp":"2026-06-01T08:25:04.044Z"}
{"type":"message","id":"0e80f313","parentId":"22a69cae","timestamp":"2026-06-01T08:25:22.204Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The owner sent the same 2 cookies again. They can't find keycloak cookies in their extension. Let me think about this differently.\n\nThe `devops_token` is a JWT. Let me decode it:\n```\neyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiJ9.eyJleHAiOjE3ODAzODI0MDMsInVzZXJfbmFtZSI6InllemhpanVuIn0.O5U10SOnXDR2Q02ZDOxG47hV3VAv65y09yDaZ-AO-bY\n```\n\nHeader: `{\"alg\":\"HS256\"}`\nPayload: `{\"exp\":1780382403,\"user_name\":\"yezhijun\"}`\n\nSo the JWT contains the username and expires at Unix timestamp 1780382403. Let me check if it's still valid.\n\nCurrent time: 2026-06-01 16:24 CST = 08:24 UTC\n1780382403 - 1780295043 (approx June 1 08:24 UTC) = 87360 seconds ≈ 24 hours\n\nSo the token expires in about 24 hours from now. But when we try to use just these 2 cookies, the Keycloak login page appears because we don't have the Keycloak SSO session cookie.\n\nThe user said they logged in via 飞书 SSO. The issue is that the 飞书 SSO flow sets cookies on the keycloak domain. Without those, even with a valid `devops_token`, the authentication might not work because the `devops_token` might be the API token but not the session token that Keycloak checks.\n\nWait, actually let me think about this more carefully. The DevOps service might use the `devops_token` as an API token directly - it's a JWT with username and expiration. If we set just this cookie and visit the DevOps page, it should work... unless the DevOps app redirects to Keycloak first before even checking the cookie.\n\nLet me try a different approach. Instead of using the keepalive script (which goes to the DevOps list page and gets redirected), let me directly access the pipeline API endpoint with the token in the header, not as a cookie.\n\nActually, let me look at the JWT more carefully:\n- `user_name`: `yezhijun`\n- `exp`: 1780382403\n\nThe token is signed with HS256. This looks like a direct DevOps API token, not a Keycloak session token. The DevOps app probably validates this JWT directly.\n\nBut the problem is that when the browser navigates to a DevOps URL, the Keycloak middleware intercepts it and redirects to login. If I directly call the DevOps API endpoints with this cookie, it might work.\n\nLet me try calling the pipeline's API directly. The DevOps API might be at something like:\n`https://devops.devcloud.ztgame.com/projects/yyzy/pipelines/p-f78c977835c84b71a6d58b4746cd1c4a/start`\nor similar.\n\nActually, I don't know the exact API endpoints. Let me try a simpler approach:\n\n1. Write a Playwright script that:\n   - Opens a headed browser\n   - Goes to the Keycloak login with devops_token cookie\n   - Waits for the user to complete login manually\n   - Saves the cookies after\n   \nBut actually, the user can't see the headed browser...\n\nOK let me try yet another approach. What if I try to use the `devops_token` as an API key in the Authorization header instead of relying on the Keycloak redirect flow?\n\nActually, let me just try to directly use the devops_token in a curl-like call to the pipeline page. If the DevOps app reads the token from cookies and doesn't require Keycloak SSO session, then it should work.\n\nLet me try with the Playwright script that:\n1. Sets only the devops cookies\n2. Directly navigates to the pipeline page\n3. But before navigation, does `page.route` to intercept the Keycloak redirect and prevent it\n4. Or, sets the `devops_token` as an Authorization header\n\nHmm, that's getting too complex. Let me try a much simpler approach:\n\nLet me use Playwright with the `--no-sandbox` argument and directly go to the pipeline page. Instead of the keepalive script's approach (which goes to pipelines list and then pipeline detail), let me go directly to the pipeline detail page. Maybe the Keycloak protection is only on certain paths.\n\nActually, the sub-agent already tried this and got redirected. Let me try calling the API directly with the token.\n\nActually, let me try another creative approach. The JWT contains `user_name: yezhijun`, so this is a JWT issued by the DevOps service, not Keycloak. Maybe I can use it to call the DevOps's own API directly, bypassing the Keycloak middleware.\n\nBut I don't know the API format. Let me try to check if there's a swagger doc, or just try some common REST API patterns.\n\nYou know what, let me just try a Playwright script that:\n1. Sets the 2 devops cookies\n2. Goes to the pipeline page directly\n3. Takes a screenshot to see what happens\n4. Logs the full network state\n\nMaybe the redirect to Keycloak then immediately redirects back because the devops_token is valid. Let me check.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"主人，扩展里没有 keycloak 域的 Cookie 对吧？那换个思路——直接用这个 `devops_token` JWT 试试能不能调通 DevOps 的 API。"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_8JYTghj86Z86QUYfyOS35983","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"// 用 devops_token JWT 直接访问 DevOps API\nimport { chromium } from 'playwright';\nimport fs from 'fs';\nimport path from 'path';\nimport { fileURLToPath } from 'url';\n\nconst __filename = fileURLToPath(import.meta.url);\nconst __dirname = path.dirname(__filename);\nconst WORKSPACE_DIR = path.resolve(__dirname, '..');\nconst COOKIES_FILE = path.join(WORKSPACE_DIR, 'devops_cookies.json');\nconst SCREENSHOT_DIR = path.join(WORKSPACE_DIR, 'memory');\n\nconst PIPELINE_URL = 'https://devops.devcloud.ztgame.com/projects/yyzy/pipelines/p-f78c977835c84b71a6d58b4746cd1c4a';\n\nfunction log(msg) { console.log(`[DEVOP] ${msg}`); }\nfunction sleep(ms) { return new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, ms)); }\n\nasync function main() {\n  log('=== 直接访问 DevOps 流水线页面 ===');\n\n  const browser = await chromium.launch({\n    headless: true,\n    args: ['--no-sandbox', '--disable-blink-features=AutomationControlled'],\n  });\n  const ctx = await browser.newContext({\n    viewport: { width: 1920, height: 1080 },\n    locale: 'zh-CN',\n    ignoreHTTPSErrors: true,\n  });\n\n  // 只设置主人给的 2 个 cookie\n  await ctx.addCookies([\n    {\n      name: 'devops_return_url',\n      value: 'https://devops.devcloud.ztgame.com/projects/yyzy/pipelines/p-f78c977835c84b71a6d58b4746cd1c4a',\n      domain: '.devcloud.ztgame.com',\n      path: '/',\n      httpOnly: false,\n      secure: false,\n      sameSite: 'None',\n      expires: 1780382398,\n    },\n    {\n      name: 'devops_token',\n      value: 'eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiJ9.eyJleHAiOjE3ODAzODI0MDMsInVzZXJfbmFtZSI6InllemhpanVuIn0.O5U10SOnXDR2Q02ZDOxG47hV3VAv65y09yDaZ-AO-bY',\n      domain: '.devcloud.ztgame.com',\n      path: '/',\n      httpOnly: false,\n      secure: false,\n      sameSite: 'None',\n      expires: 1780382404.043704,\n    }\n  ]);\n\n  const page = await ctx.newPage();\n\n  // 监听网络请求，看看是否有 API 调用\n  const apiCalls = [];\n  page.on('response', response => {\n    const url = response.url();\n    if (url.includes('/api/') || url.includes('/v1/') || url.includes('devops') || url.includes('pipeline')) {\n      apiCalls.push({ url: url.substring(0, 200), status: response.status() });\n    }\n  });\n\n  log('访问流水线页面...');\n  await page.goto(PIPELINE_URL, { waitUntil: 'networkidle', timeout: 30000 });\n  await sleep(5000);\n\n  const currentUrl = page.url();\n  const title = await page.title();\n  log(`最终 URL: ${currentUrl}`);\n  log(`页面标题: ${title}`);\n\n  await page.screenshot({ path: path.join(SCREENSHOT_DIR, 'devops_direct.png'), fullPage: true });\n  log('截图已保存');\n\n  // 输出 API 调用\n  log(`API 调用数量: ${apiCalls.length}`);\n  apiCalls.slice(0, 20).forEach(c => log(`  ${c.status} ${c.url}`));\n\n  // 检查是否成功进入\n  if (!currentUrl.includes('keycloak') && !currentUrl.includes('login')) {\n    log('✅ 成功进入 DevOps！');\n    \n    // 尝试找「启动新构建」按钮\n    const buttons = await page.$$eval('button, a, span, div', els => \n      els.filter(e => e.textContent.includes('启动') || e.textContent.includes('新构建') || e.textContent.includes('Run'))\n        .map(e => ({ text: e.textContent.substring(0, 50), tag: e.tagName }))\n    );\n    log(`找到的按钮: ${JSON.stringify(buttons)}`);\n\n    // 保存 Cookie（此刻的完整 Cookie 集）\n    const fullCookies = await ctx.cookies();\n    const devopsCookies = fullCookies.filter(c => \n      c.domain.includes('devcloud.ztgame.com') || c.domain.includes('keycloak')\n    );\n    fs.writeFileSync(COOKIES_FILE, JSON.stringify(devopsCookies, null, 2));\n    log(`✅ 已保存 ${devopsCookies.length} 个 DevOps Cookie`);\n  } else {\n    log('❌ 被重定向到 Keycloak 登录页');\n    // 检查页面内容\n    const bodyText = await page.evaluate(() => document.body.innerText.substring(0, 1000));\n    log(`页面内容: ${bodyText.substring(0, 300)}`);\n  }\n\n  await browser.close();\n}\n\nmain().catch(e => {\n  log(`ERROR: ${e.message}`);\n  process.exit(1);\n});\n","path":"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\workspace\\scripts\\devops_test_cookies.mjs"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":864,"output":2469,"cacheRead":46848,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":50181,"cost":{"input":0.00012096000000000001,"output":0.00069132,"cacheRead":0.0013117439999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.002124024}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780302304045,"responseId":"b3d7ee76-4bc8-4439-978c-4812995045d6"}}
