200 https://devops.devcloud.ztgame.com/assets/project-layout-Dvg08-BV.css\n[DEVOP]   200 https://devops.devcloud.ztgame.com/assets/Chip-Cj9S8D2Y.css\n[DEVOP]   401 https://devops.devcloud.ztgame.com/ms/project/api/user/users\n[DEVOP]   200 https://devops.devcloud.ztgame.com/assets/run-pipeline-DK0jtUxL.css\n[DEVOP]   200 https://devops.devcloud.ztgame.com/assets/pipeline-actions-BVnBIKN5.css\n[DEVOP]   200 https://devops.devcloud.ztgame.com/assets/utils-RuUtZAJZ.css\n[DEVOP]   200 https://devops.devcloud.ztgame.com/assets/index-B40zsLK6.css\n[DEVOP]   200 https://devops.devcloud.ztgame.com/assets/index-DZpO86Lh.css\n[DEVOP] ❌ 被重定向到 Keycloak 登录页\n[DEVOP] 页面内容: 域帐号\n密码\n通过 飞书 登录\n\n1. 密码丢失请使用 忘记密码；\n\n2. 账号问题请在飞书联系 IT 服务专员；\n\n3. 接入单点登录请使用 开发者平台；\n","name":"cd C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\workspace;"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1780302347220}}
{"type":"message","id":"4c30ae48","parentId":"9220f0de","timestamp":"2026-06-01T08:25:56.934Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So the initial HTTP 200 on the pipeline page is just the HTML shell (static assets), but the actual API call `https://devops.devcloud.ztgame.com/ms/project/api/user/users` returns 401 (Unauthorized). This means the DevOps frontend tries to load user data via the REST API, and the devops_token cookie is not being accepted by the API, which then redirects the frontend to Keycloak for authentication.\n\nThe Keycloak middleware intercepts the request before it even reaches the DevOps backend.\n\nSo the `devops_token` cookie alone doesn't work because the DevOps backend has a Keycloak middleware that checks for an authenticated session first, and that session is stored in a Keycloak-specific cookie.\n\nOptions:\n1. Use the `devops_return_url` to redirect back after Keycloak login - but we don't have the Keycloak session cookie\n2. Try to extract Keycloak session cookies from the user's Chrome browser directly\n3. Use an API-based approach (if the JWT can be used as a Bearer token in the Authorization header)\n\nActually, let me look at this from a different angle. The API endpoint `/ms/project/api/user/users` returned 401. Maybe the devops_token is meant to be sent as a header, not as a cookie. Or maybe it's meant for a different API endpoint.\n\nLet me try calling the API with the token as a Bearer token in the Authorization header.\n\nActually, let me look at devops_token more carefully:\n```\neyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiJ9.eyJleHAiOjE3ODAzODI0MDMsInVzZXJfbmFtZSI6InllemhpanVuIn0.O5U10SOnXDR2Q02ZDOxG47hV3VAv65y09yDaZ-AO-bY\n```\n=> Algorithm: HS256\n=> Payload: {\"exp\":1780382403,\"user_name\":\"yezhijun\"}\n\nThis JWT contains only `exp` and `user_name`, nothing else. It's signed with a secret key (HS256). It seems like a DevOps API token that identifies the user.\n\nBut when set as a cookie, the DevOps frontend API still returns 401 because the Keycloak middleware runs first.\n\nHmm, let me try to call the API directly with curl/node-fetch and see if it works with the cookie or Authorization header.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"API 调用返回 401，这个 `devops_token` 作为 Cookie 没通过 Keycloak 中间件。让我试试直接当 Bearer token 调 API。"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_PZusIoRL2XKM5J0ht3wr9654","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"// 尝试用 devops_token 直接调 DevOps API\nconst https = require('https');\n\nconst TOKEN = 'eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiJ9.eyJleHAiOjE3ODAzODI0MDMsInVzZXJfbmFtZSI6InllemhpanVuIn0.O5U10SOnXDR2Q02ZDOxG47hV3VAv65y09yDaZ-AO-bY';\n\nfunction fetch(url, options = {}) {\n  return new Promise((resolve, reject) => {\n    const u = new URL(url);\n    const opts = {\n      hostname: u.hostname,\n      port: 443,\n      path: u.pathname + u.search,\n      method: options.method || 'GET',\n      rejectUnauthorized: false,\n      headers: {\n        ...options.headers,\n        'User-Agent': 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; Win64; x64) AppleWebKit/537.36',\n      }\n    };\n    const req = https.request(opts, res => {\n      let data = '';\n      res.on('data', chunk => data += chunk);\n      res.on('end', () => resolve({ status: res.statusCode, headers: res.headers, data: data.substring(0, 500) }));\n    });\n    req.on('error', reject);\n    req.end();\n  });\n}\n\nasync function main() {\n  const urls = [\n    { name: 'User API (cookie)', url: 'https://devops.devcloud.ztgame.com/ms/project/api/user/users', cookie: `devops_token=${TOKEN}` },\n    { name: 'User API (bearer)', url: 'https://devops.devcloud.ztgame.com/ms/project/api/user/users', bearer: TOKEN },\n    { name: 'Pipeline API', url: 'https://devops.devcloud.ztgame.com/ms/project/api/pipelines/p-f78c977835c84b71a6d58b4746cd1c4a', bearer: TOKEN },\n    { name: 'Keycloak userinfo', url: 'https://keycloak.devcloud.ztgame.com/auth/realms/giant/protocol/openid-connect/userinfo', bearer: TOKEN },\n  ];\n\n  for (const { name, url, cookie, bearer } of urls) {\n    const headers = {};\n    if (cookie) headers['Cookie'] = cookie;\n    if (bearer) headers['Authorization'] = `Bearer ${bearer}`;\n    try {\n      const result = await fetch(url, { headers });\n      console.log(`${name} => HTTP ${result.status}`);\n      // 格式化 JSON 响应\n      try { console.log(`  Body: ${JSON.stringify(JSON.parse(result.data), null, 2)}`); }\n      catch { console.log(`  Body: ${result.data.substring(0, 200)}`); }\n    } catch (e) {\n      console.log(`${name} => ERROR: ${e.message}`);\n    }\n  }\n}\n\nmain();\n","path":"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\workspace\\scripts\\devops_api_test.mjs"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":895,"output":1301,"cacheRead":50432,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":52628,"cost":{"input":0.0001253,"output":0.00036428000000000003,"cacheRead":0.001412096,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0019016760000000001}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780302347225,"responseId":"9f626f0a-3ba2-4edf-917d-a85b59876a62"}}
