{"type":"message","id":"5dc4ca21","parentId":"aa5817fa","timestamp":"2026-06-01T08:27:41.753Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_ET_HKJE5P87NmcimElXQ52a7771","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"📁 assets/pipeline-BIYBRy-m.js (1KB)\n\n📁 assets/stop-pipeline-ZEQG7a8a.js (1KB)\n\n📁 assets/pipeline-actions-DpEEARm-.js (9KB)\n  🎯 build-duration\n  🎯 build-distance\n\n📁 assets/run-pipeline.vue_vue_type_script_setup_true_lang-BR54bnqp.js (99KB)\n  🎯 start\n  🎯 vmBuild\n  🎯 run-pipeline\n  🎯 started"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":596,"aggregated":"📁 assets/pipeline-BIYBRy-m.js (1KB)\n\n📁 assets/stop-pipeline-ZEQG7a8a.js (1KB)\n\n📁 assets/pipeline-actions-DpEEARm-.js (9KB)\n  🎯 build-duration\n  🎯 build-distance\n\n📁 assets/run-pipeline.vue_vue_type_script_setup_true_lang-BR54bnqp.js (99KB)\n  🎯 start\n  🎯 vmBuild\n  🎯 run-pipeline\n  🎯 started","cwd":"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1780302461753}}
{"type":"message","id":"9e131d75","parentId":"5dc4ca21","timestamp":"2026-06-01T08:27:49.424Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The `pipeline-actions-DpEEARm-.js` file is only 9KB and contains the pipeline actions. Let me try to deobfuscate it. It has \"build-duration\" and \"build-distance\". Let me fetch the whole content and search more carefully.\n\nBut actually, the `run-pipeline.vue` file is 99KB and it's the one that actually calls the APIs. Let me look at its content more carefully, especially looking for URL patterns with different quote styles.\n\nActually, the key insight might be that the API endpoints use string concatenation and are built dynamically, so my regex didn't catch them. Let me dump more of the file.\n\nActually, let me try a completely different approach. Since I can't easily figure out the API routes from the JS code, let me try to use Playwright with a Keycloak login bypass.\n\nThe Keycloak login page has a \"通过飞书登录\" button. When I click it, it redirects to Feishu SSO which shows a QR code. The user can scan that QR code with their Feishu app.\n\nThe issue earlier was that I couldn't show the QR code to the user because the image model was broken.\n\nBut wait - maybe I can send the QR code image directly through the Feishu messaging system using MEDIA? Or I can convert the QR code to text and send it?\n\nNo... QR codes are images, can't send as text.\n\nLet me try another approach: use Playwright to intercept the Feishu QR code page, extract the QR code URL, encode it, and then send a link the user can click instead.\n\nOr... let me check the login page on all browsers to see if there's an alternative - like email/password login for the domain account.\n\nActually, wait - the Keycloak login page has \"域帐号\" and \"密码\" fields. I know the username is \"yezhijun\" (from the JWT). Does the user know their password? If I can ask the user to tell me their domain password, I can automate the login.\n\nNo, that's a security issue. Let me ask the user for a different approach.\n\nActually, let me think about this differently. The user was able to log into DevOps via Chrome earlier. The Chrome session cookies (keycloak session) are somewhere in Chrome's user data. The issue is that when I tried to use `launchPersistentContext`, Chrome was already running.\n\nWhat if I close Chrome, then use Playwright to launch it? That would work but would disrupt whatever the user is doing.\n\nActually, let me try to use Chrome's remote debugging port feature. If Chrome is running with `--remote-debugging-port=9222`, I can connect to it via CDP. But Chrome probably wasn't started with that flag.\n\nLet me ask the user to:\n1. Close Chrome completely\n2. Let me extract the cookies via Playwright\n\nOr, better idea: Let me check if there's a way to read Chrome's cookie file directly. On Windows, Chrome cookies are stored in `AppData\\Local\\Google\\Chrome\\User Data\\Default\\Network\\Cookies` but they're encrypted with the Windows Data Protection API (DPAPI). So I'd need to decrypt them...\n\nLet me try one more creative approach. Since the user can export cookies from Chrome's Cookie Editor extension, let me ask them to specifically look for cookies under `keycloak.devcloud.ztgame.com` domain. Maybe the extension shows them by default by domain.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"JS 文件被混淆了，API 路由不好挖。换个思路——主人，麻烦在 Cookie 扩展里搜一下 **`keycloak`** 关键字的 Cookie，或者看看有没有按域名分组的，把 `keycloak.devcloud.ztgame.com` 下的全部导出来~\n\n或者更简单：**Chrome 完全关掉**，我用 Playwright 帮你直接开了取 Cookie，几秒钟搞定。"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":169,"output":830,"cacheRead":65920,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":66919,"cost":{"input":0.00002366,"output":0.0002324,"cacheRead":0.00184576,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00210182}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1780302461755,"responseId":"21f026d5-cd50-4401-a2d7-3166a1a04769"}}
