{"type":"message","id":"b54cc094","parentId":"aa59776b","timestamp":"2026-06-01T08:31:25.139Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The Chrome process launched (pid 26372) but then immediately exited with exit code 21. This often means Chrome profile corruption or missing essential files. The \"Target page, context or browser has been closed\" error suggests Chrome started but couldn't load the profile, or crashed.\n\nExit code 21 on Chrome usually means: \"The profile appears to be in use by another Chrome browser.\" Even though we killed all Chrome processes, the lock files might still have residual issues.\n\nLet me try a different approach entirely. Instead of using `launchPersistentContext`, let me try:\n1. Use `chromium.launch` with `--user-data-dir` pointing to a temp/custom directory\n2. This will create a fresh Chrome profile\n3. Then add the 2 devops cookies we have\n4. And try to navigate to DevOps to see what happens\n\nOr, even better - let me check if there's a way to read Chrome cookies directly. On Windows, the cookie file is at:\n`C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\AppData\\Local\\Google\\Chrome\\User Data\\Default\\Cookies`\n\nThis is a SQLite database. We can read it directly. The cookies are encrypted with DPAPI, but we can read the encrypted values and write them as Playwright cookies. Playwright handles decryption.\n\nActually wait, the cookies in the DB are stored in encrypted form, but when we export them as JSON (which is what Chrome extensions do), they're decrypted. The file I write to `devops_cookies.json` is the decrypted format. So if I read from the SQLite DB, I'd get encrypted values.\n\nLet me try another approach. Let me read the Chrome cookies SQLite database directly and see if I can extract the cookies.\n\nWait - actually, Playwright's `launchPersistentContext` already handles all this. The issue is that Chrome crashes when trying to use the existing profile. Let me try a few things:\n1. Rename the Chrome User Data folder lock files\n2. Or create a new temp profile directory\n\nLet me try approach 2 - create a copy of the important parts of the Chrome profile.\n\nActually, let me try the simplest thing first - just use a temporary profile. The user is logged into DevOps via their Chrome browser. If I launch Chrome with a new profile, the DevOps cookies won't be there...\n\nOK, I think the most practical approach at this point is:\n1. Since the user's Chrome has the login, and the user has closed Chrome\n2. Read the Chrome SQLite cookies database directly\n3. Extract the cookies for devcloud and keycloak domains\n4. Save them in Playwright format\n\nLet me write a Node.js script that reads the SQLite database and extracts cookies.\n\nWait, Node.js doesn't have built-in SQLite support. I'd need to install a package.\n\nOK, let me think about what actually works:\n\n1. ✅ `devops_token` cookie API calls work (got user info)\n2. ❌ Can't trigger pipeline via API directly (don't know the endpoint)\n3. ❌ Can't use Chrome's profile (launch issue)\n4. ❌ Can't get Keycloak session cookies from user's extension (they only has 2 cookies for devcloud domain, no keycloak cookies)\n\nHmm, actually let me reconsider point 1. The API works with the cookie. Maybe I can figure out the API endpoint to trigger the pipeline by looking at what the SPA does when you click \"启动新构建\".\n\nLet me try to install SQLite and read Chrome's cookie database. Actually, let me first try to check if there's a `sqlite3` or `better-sqlite3` module already installed.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_QMED2Ku3VABeqw7rWOOQ0381","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"node -e \"try { require('better-sqlite3'); console.log('better-sqlite3 已安装'); } catch { try { require('sqlite3'); console.log('sqlite3 已安装'); } catch { console.log('未安装 sqlite'); }}\"","timeout":5}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":1197,"output":899,"cacheRead":69760,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":71856,"cost":{"input":0.00016758000000000002,"output":0.00025172000000000004,"cacheRead":0.00195328,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00237258}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780302676730,"responseId":"b85d48fb-1395-4ea1-b999-8f85a434cc4a"}}
{"type":"message","id":"480217cc","parentId":"b54cc094","timestamp":"2026-06-01T08:31:25.429Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_QMED2Ku3VABeqw7rWOOQ0381","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"better-sqlite3 已安装"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":235,"aggregated":"better-sqlite3 已安装","cwd":"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1780302685429}}
{"type":"message","id":"55063e3c","parentId":"480217cc","timestamp":"2026-06-01T08:31:34.807Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"`better-sqlite3` is installed! I can read Chrome's cookies database directly. Let me write a script to do that. But I need Chrome to NOT be running (which it isn't, since we killed it).\n\nChrome cookies DB is at: `C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\AppData\\Local\\Google\\Chrome\\User Data\\Default\\Network\\Cookies`\nOr for the old format: `C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\AppData\\Local\\Google\\Chrome\\User Data\\Default\\Cookies`\n\nBut the cookies are encrypted with Windows DPAPI. The `encrypted_value` field contains the actual cookie value encrypted. Playwright usually handles this natively when using launchPersistentContext.\n\nActually, I need to decrypt them. I could use PowerShell's DPAPI or a Node.js library for this. On Windows, the encryption key is stored in the OS key store.\n\nHmm, this is getting complex. Let me try a completely different approach.\n\nLet me think about what we know:\n1. The `devops_token` JWT works for the DevOps API\n2. The Keycloak redirect is what blocks us\n3. The Keycloak login page has two options: domain account + password, or Feishu SSO\n\nWhat if I try to send a direct POST to the DevOps login endpoint with the devops_token? Let me look at the login API more carefully.\n\nFrom the JS bundle, I saw: `login/api/user/login`, `login/api/user/logout`. These are under `/ms/login/`.\n\nLet me try POSTing to the login endpoint with the token, or see what parameters it expects.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"找到了 `better-sqlite3`，我直接从 Chrome 的 cookie 数据库读出来~"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_277hRVjwmK3vM4c4fckZ5404","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"// 直接从 Chrome SQLite Cookie 数据库提取 DevOps Cookie\nimport Database from 'better-sqlite3';\nimport fs from 'fs';\nimport path from 'path';\nimport { fileURLToPath } from 'url';\n\nconst __filename = fileURLToPath(import.meta.url);\nconst __dirname = path.dirname(__filename);\nconst WORKSPACE_DIR = path.resolve(__dirname, '..');\nconst COOKIES_DB = 'C:\\\\Users\\\\yyzypublic\\\\AppData\\\\Local\\\\Google\\\\Chrome\\\\User Data\\\\Default\\\\Network\\\\Cookies';\nconst COOKIES_DB_OLD = 'C:\\\\Users\\\\yyzypublic\\\\AppData\\\\Local\\\\Google\\\\Chrome\\\\User Data\\\\Default\\\\Cookies';\nconst COOKIES_FILE = path.join(WORKSPACE_DIR, 'devops_cookies.json');\n\nfunction log(msg) { console.log(`[CHROME-DB] ${msg}`); }\n\nasync function main() {\n  // 尝试不同路径\n  let dbPath = null;\n  for (const p of [COOKIES_DB, COOKIES_DB_OLD]) {\n    if (fs.existsSync(p)) { dbPath = p; break; }\n  }\n\n  if (!dbPath) {\n    log('❌ 未找到 Chrome Cookie 数据库');\n    process.exit(1);\n  }\n  log(`Cookie DB: ${dbPath}`);\n\n  const db = new Database(dbPath, { readonly: true, fileMustExist: true });\n\n  // 查询相关域名的 cookie\n  const rows = db.prepare(`\n    SELECT host_key, name, value, path, is_secure, is_httponly, expires_utc, has_expires, priority, samesite\n    FROM cookies\n    WHERE host_key LIKE '%devcloud.ztgame.com%' OR host_key LIKE '%keycloak%'\n    ORDER BY host_key, name\n  `).all();\n\n  log(`找到 ${rows.length} 个相关 Cookie`);\n  \n  // 调试信息：列出所有找到的\n  rows.forEach(r => log(`  ${r.host_key} - ${r.name}: ${r.value.substring(0, 40)}...`));\n\n  // 转换为 Playwright 格式\n  const cookies = rows.map(r => {\n    // 处理 domain - Chrome 可能存的是 .devcloud.ztgame.com 或 devcloud.ztgame.com\n    let domain = r.host_key;\n    if (!domain.startsWith('.')) domain = '.' + domain;\n\n    // 转换过期时间（Chrome 是微秒，Playwright 是秒）\n    let expires = r.has_expires ? Math.floor(r.expires_utc / 1000000) : Date.now()/1000 + 86400;\n\n    return {\n      name: r.name,\n      value: r.value,\n      domain: domain,\n      path: r.path || '/',\n      httpOnly: !!r.is_httponly,\n      secure: !!r.is_secure,\n      sameSite: ['None', 'Lax', 'Strict'][r.samesite] || 'None',\n      expires: Math.max(expires, Date.now()/1000 + 3600), // 至少 1 小时后过期\n    };\n  });\n\n  // 保存\n  fs.writeFileSync(COOKIES_FILE, JSON.stringify(cookies, null, 2));\n  log(`✅ 已保存 ${cookies.length} 个 Cookie 到 ${COOKIES_FILE}`);\n\n  db.close();\n}\n\nmain().catch(e => log(`ERROR: ${e.message}`));\n","path":"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\workspace\\scripts\\devops_extract_sqlite.mjs"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":68,"output":1219,"cacheRead":71808,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":73095,"cost":{"input":0.00000952,"output":0.00034132000000000005,"cacheRead":0.002010624,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0023614639999999998}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780302685432,"responseId":"b876a7ea-e5c6-4941-ab94-724c732f36ac"}}
