{"type":"message","id":"9747ce9e","parentId":"a8d2e059","timestamp":"2026-06-01T08:31:39.060Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Wait, I need to reconsider. Chrome cookie values in the DB are encrypted with Windows DPAPI. The `value` field we read might be garbage or empty. Let me check what the DB actually stores.\n\nActually, in older Chrome versions (< Chrome 80), cookies were stored unencrypted in `Cookies` table with a plain `value` column. But since Chrome 80+, they use encrypted values.\n\nThe `encrypted_value` column contains the DPAPI-encrypted data. Playwright natively handles decryption when using `launchPersistentContext`.\n\nHowever, on newer Chrome, the `value` column might return empty and `encrypted_value` column contains the real encrypted data.\n\nLet me adjust the query to also read `encrypted_value`, and then try to decrypt it using Windows DPAPI.\n\nActually, let me first just try running it and see what values come back. If they're encrypted/garbage, I'll adjust.\n\nActually, since Chrome 108+, even the `Cookies` table format changed. Let me just try it and see.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_jBXUKc90jLst6XvDBSrl8578","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\workspace; node scripts/devops_extract_sqlite.mjs","timeout":10}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":54,"output":306,"cacheRead":73088,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":73448,"cost":{"input":0.0000075600000000000005,"output":0.00008568,"cacheRead":0.002046464,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.002139704}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780302694828,"responseId":"c8968215-3b48-4df4-9c52-c8800ddeed21"}}
