{"type":"message","id":"00e796b6","parentId":"5f322054","timestamp":"2026-06-01T08:32:04.267Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Also I realize the cookies in Chrome are stored encrypted. The `value` column in the `cookies` table contains the actual value but it's DPAPI-encrypted for cookies set with `httponly` or `secure` flags. Some cookies might have plaintext values though.\n\nActually, in Chrome 127+, the cookie values are all encrypted with AES-256-GCM, with the key stored in the OS keychain (DPAPI on Windows). The `encrypted_value` column in the database stores the raw encrypted blob.\n\nThis means I can't decrypt the cookies without knowing the encryption key. The encryption key is stored in Chrome's \"Local State\" file at `%LOCALAPPDATA%\\Google\\Chrome\\User Data\\Local State`, and it's DPAPI-encrypted.\n\nThis is getting way too complex. Let me try a completely different approach.\n\nLet me just try to open the DB directly without copying, using `PRAGMA locking_mode = EXCLUSIVE` or `PRAGMA query_only = 1`.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_zPnCuXiRdXhAmFM4LCum1547","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\workspace; node scripts/devops_extract_sqlite.mjs","timeout":10}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":111,"output":302,"cacheRead":75520,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":75933,"cost":{"input":0.00001554,"output":0.00008456,"cacheRead":0.00211456,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0022146600000000002}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780302720855,"responseId":"ac5f4948-58a2-42f2-87d2-e1e3a4301806"}}
