{"type":"message","id":"4a47a720","parentId":"b4828945","timestamp":"2026-06-01T08:33:11.442Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Still SIGKILL'd. The `launchPersistentContext` is having issues. It might be crashing internally. \n\nLet me try a completely different approach. Instead of using Playwright's persistent context, let me:\n1. Launch a regular Playwright browser with a fresh temp profile\n2. Use `page.addInitScript` to inject a script that reads the Chrome profile cookies via DPAPI\n3. Or better - just use the API with the devops_token cookie we already have\n\nActually, wait. Let me try the simplest thing: use `launchPersistentContext` but without `channel: 'chrome'`. This will use Playwright's bundled Chromium instead of system Chrome.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_0MJlhZQSH0Z3WCXKvqCJ5438","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\workspace\\scripts\\devops_extract_chrome2.mjs","edits":[{"oldText":"  const browser = await chromium.launchPersistentContext(CHROME_PROFILE, {\n    headless: true,\n    channel: 'chrome',\n    args: ['--no-sandbox'],\n    ignoreHTTPSErrors: true,\n  });","newText":"  const browser = await chromium.launchPersistentContext(CHROME_PROFILE, {\n    headless: true,\n    args: ['--no-sandbox'],\n    ignoreHTTPSErrors: true,\n  });"}]}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":184,"output":351,"cacheRead":79744,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":80279,"cost":{"input":0.00002576,"output":0.00009828,"cacheRead":0.002232832,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0023568720000000003}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780302787983,"responseId":"bf53fa1b-73b0-436b-ae3f-838aabeb8539"}}
