{"type":"message","id":"f972d8ee","parentId":"71276c67","timestamp":"2026-06-01T08:34:56.748Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Wait, I also need to look at what the manualStartupPipeline actually sends in the body. Let me look at the run-pipeline.vue code which uses this function. \n\nFrom the code I saw earlier:\n```\nconst{id:s}=await manualStartupPipeline(a.projectCode,a.pipelineId,{docker_config_map:JSON.stringify(w),docker_server:i.value.server.join(...})\n```\n\nAnd also:\n```\nconst{id:m}=await manualStartupPipeline(t.projectCode,t.pipelineId,k)\n```\nwhere `k={}` or variables.\n\nSo the function signature is `manualStartupPipeline(projectCode, pipelineId, variables)`. The API POSTs to `process/api/user/builds/{projectCode}/{pipelineId}` with the body being the variables/dest.\n\nBut I need to understand the exact body format. Let me check what `getManualStartupInfo` returns - specifically the `properties` field which specifies the available parameters.\n\nActually, let me also look at how the manual trigger form is rendered in the UI. From the run-pipeline.vue, I saw references to variables and start parameters.\n\nLet me just try the trigger with different body formats and see what works.\n\nActually, looking at the code more carefully from the earlier snippet:\n```javascript\nconst _=T.filter(L=>L.displayConfig!==VARIABLE_DISPLAY_CONFIG.NOT_DISPLAY);\nm||_.length?l.value=!0:i()\n```\n\nAnd:\n```javascript\nconst{id:m}=await manualStartupPipeline(t.projectCode,t.pipelineId,k)\n```\n\nWhere `i()` calls `manualStartupPipeline(...)` with `k` being the collected variables.\n\nI think the body structure for the POST should be the variables object. Let me try with `{dest: '1v1_test'}` first.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_6sAwA2gWrzve5MA686v41695","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\workspace; node scripts/devops_trigger_v2.mjs","timeout":20}