{"type":"message","id":"925dff49","parentId":"6cc698ca","timestamp":"2026-06-01T08:37:50.601Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Still pending. The detailed endpoint might not return the correct status. Let me check if maybe the build history endpoint gives us more info. Or maybe the detail endpoint returns status differently.\n\nLet me also check if there's a different build status field. The original code has a function for getting build history that takes query parameters including buildNo, and another for getting detail. Let me also check the build list endpoint for the pipeline.\n\nActually, looking at the code, the `_` function fetches the build history:\n```\n_=async(e,t,s)=>{\n    const n=\"process/api/user/builds/\".concat(e,\"/\").concat(t,\"/history/new?\").concat(c(s));\n    return await a.get(n)\n}\n```\n\nThe query params are serialized by the `c` function which converts an object to URL params.\n\nAnd the `ee` function gets the build condition status:\n```\nee=async(e,t)=>{\n    const s=\"process/api/user/builds/\".concat(e,\"/\").concat(t,\"/historyCondition/status\");\n    return await a.get(s)\n}\n```\n\nLet me try the history endpoint to see the build status.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_ldduNvrbfHWaa1QjG8vH4889","name":"process","arguments":{"sessionId":"neat-otter","action":"kill"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":127,"output":297,"cacheRead":104192,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":104616,"cost":{"input":0.000017780000000000003,"output":0.00008316000000000001,"cacheRead":0.0029173759999999997,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0030183159999999996}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780303066774,"responseId":"40cd3f4e-9ca1-4cce-a440-e64739fa76de"}}
